narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I think this class is fantastic. It is very small so it is basically like a seminar and you get a lot of attention in class. Also you learn a lot in one semester. I would absolutely recommend it to any student interested in taking an African language.
Great introductory course to the language.
A good way to fulfill the language requirement. Yoruba itself is not an easy language, but the professor tries his best to make it easy. A little messy sometimes though!
Take Yoruba if you can. You won't regret it.
